  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "Naturally occurring compounds called <i>cyanogenic glycosides,</i> such as lotaustralin, release hydrogen cyanide, HCN, when treated with aqueous acid. The reaction occurs by hydrolysis of the acetal linkage to form a cyanohydrin, which then expels HCN and gives a carbonyl compound.",
